  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's possible that that's the reason why they decided they couldn't bother going to this little village and finding me there, but I stayed there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the end of the war came in January 18, 1945, when the Russian front came by.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Before that the Germans would take us and have us to build-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I don't know what the name of it is.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were supposed to have a line of defense so they made us build-- dig big crisscross kind of a things in which soldiers would be there and defending and so on.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They got the farmers to cut trees in the forest and build fortifications, and I was given little cards.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was standing there, and I was supposed to give each of the farmers a card each time they brought a tree.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they had to bring a minimum of three trees a day before they were able to go home.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I, of course, would give them two cards, hoping that the Germans are not going to find out-- which they didn't-- so they could go home sooner.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was a part of Poland which was annexed to Germany, and there was a part of Poland which was-- I don't know what they call it.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In Polish it was [POLISH], which is part of Poland which was under the German occupation but was not part of Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the border was about 20 kilometers from where we were.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So in order for me to, again, make some money, I would take a wagon with a horse, and I would go across the border-- we were able to do that-- and smuggle food back and forth.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
